---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="The story behind StepD Music — a stepdad and his stepdaughters making video game inspired music together.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <p class="text-[0.75rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[var(--color-accent)] mb-4">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-[2.25rem] md:text-[3rem] font-black leading-tight tracking-tight mb-10">
      Gaming adventures<br />turned into songs.
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-[1.05rem] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        StepD is a music collaboration between a stepdad and his stepdaughters, turning our gaming adventures into songs and capturing how we're growing together along the way.
      </p>
      <p>
        It's part storytelling, part inside jokes, part family time: we craft lyrics together, compose in our home studio, and embrace the AI tools that are already an integral part of their lives.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our debut album <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">Tales from Topside</strong> is inspired by <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">ARC Raiders</strong> — 10 tracks that capture everything from camping snipers to desperate extractions to the trust issues that come with meeting strangers in-game.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
      <h2 class="text-[1.25rem] font-bold mb-4">What's next</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        Our second album <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">Control</strong> is in the works. Whether the next one comes from a game, a road trip, or a random Tuesday — we just follow whatever inspires us.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
